Kenya’s Housing Finance Gains, Net Interest Income Seen Growing

-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 
2011-10-13T13:00:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-13/kenya-s-housing-finance-gains-net-interest-income-seen-growing.html
Housing Finance Ltd.,  Kenya ’s only
publicly traded mortgage lender, gained for the first day in
five trading sessions on expectations its net interest income
will grow.  The company’s shares climbed 0.6 percent to 16 shillings as
of 2:02 p.m. in the capital, Nairobi, the biggest intraday gain
since Oct. 6.  “There are positive sentiments about the third-quarter,”
net interest income, said George Bodo, an equity strategist at
Nairobi-based Apex Africa Capital Ltd, adding he forecasts
quarterly net interest income growth of as much as 10 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Ombok in Nairobi at 
